Appendix G: Stochastic Intentional Flows

G.1 Langevin Dynamics on Manifolds

Definition G.1 (Langevin SDE). On a Riemannian manifold (M, g), the Langevin SDE for a potential \mathcal{L}_\lambda is:

d\theta_t = -\operatorname{grad}_g \mathcal{L}_\lambda(\theta_t) \, dt + \sqrt{2\beta^{-1}} \, dW_t,

where dW_t is the Brownian motion on M (generated by the Laplace-Beltrami operator \Delta_g).

Definition G.2 (Generator). The infinitesimal generator of this diffusion is:

\mathcal{L} = \Delta_g - \operatorname{grad}_g \mathcal{L}_\lambda \cdot \nabla = e^{\beta \mathcal{L}_\lambda} \operatorname{div}_g \left( e^{-\beta \mathcal{L}_\lambda} \nabla \right).

Proposition G.3 (Invariant measure). The unique invariant measure of the Langevin diffusion is the Gibbs measure:

\pi(d\theta) = \frac{1}{Z} e^{-\beta \mathcal{L}_\lambda(\theta)} \operatorname{vol}_g(d\theta),

where Z = \int_M e^{-\beta \mathcal{L}_\lambda} \operatorname{vol}_g is the partition function.

G.2 Bakry-Émery Theory

Definition G.4 (Curvature-dimension condition). The generator \mathcal{L} satisfies the curvature-dimension condition CD(\rho, \infty) if

\Gamma_2(f) \ge \rho \Gamma(f),

where \Gamma(f) = \frac{1}{2} \mathcal{L}(f^2) - f\mathcal{L}f is the carré du champ operator, and \Gamma_2 is its iterated version.

Theorem G.5 (Bakry-Émery criterion). For the Langevin diffusion,

\Gamma_2(f) = \|\nabla^2 f\|^2_{\text{HS}} + (\operatorname{Ric}_g + \nabla^2 \mathcal{L}_\lambda)(\nabla f, \nabla f).

Thus CD(\rho, \infty) holds with \rho = \min_{x \in M} \lambda_{\min}(\operatorname{Ric}_g(x) + \nabla^2 \mathcal{L}_\lambda(x)).

Corollary G.6 (Log-Sobolev inequality). Under CD(\rho, \infty) with \rho > 0, the invariant measure \pi satisfies a log-Sobolev inequality with constant \rho:

\operatorname{Ent}_\pi(f^2) \le \frac{2}{\rho} \mathcal{E}(f,f),

where \mathcal{E}(f,f) = \int \Gamma(f) d\pi is the Dirichlet form.

G.3 Convergence to Equilibrium

Theorem G.7 (Exponential convergence). Under the assumptions of Theorem 4.3 (with \operatorname{Ric}_g \ge \rho g and \nabla^2 \mathcal{L}_\lambda \ge \mu g), the Langevin diffusion converges exponentially to \pi in relative entropy:

\operatorname{Ent}_\pi(P_t f) \le e^{-2\alpha t} \operatorname{Ent}_\pi(f),

where \alpha = \mu + \rho and P_t is the semigroup of the diffusion.

Proof. The Bakry-Émery criterion gives CD(\alpha, \infty) with \alpha = \mu + \rho. This implies a log-Sobolev inequality with constant \alpha, which in turn implies exponential convergence in entropy . ∎

Corollary G.8 (Convergence in \chi^2 divergence). Under the same conditions,

\chi^2(P_t f \parallel \pi) \le e^{-2\alpha t} \chi^2(f \parallel \pi).

